---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import Terminal from '@/components/Terminal.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Flow Agents — Structured workflows for coding agents · Kontour AI"
  description="Flow Agents installs workflow-aware agent bundles for Claude Code, Codex, Kiro, and GitHub Actions — one structured path from idea to release readiness, with evidence the agent reads back."
>
  <Nav active="flow-agents" />

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Hero
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="contour-bg" style="
    padding: 10rem var(--spacing-page) 6rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  ">
    <div style="
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      right: 10%;
      width: 680px;
      height: 460px;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(225,221,211,0.045) 0%, transparent 68%);
      pointer-events: none;
    "></div>

    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; z-index: 1;">
      <div class="stack-mobile" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 5rem;
        align-items: center;
      ">
        <div>
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
            <span class="trust-badge trust-badge--proposed">early access</span>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3);">bash install.sh /path/to/workspace</span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="animate-fade-up" style="
            font-family: var(--font-display);
            font-optical-sizing: auto;
            font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem);
            font-weight: 400;
            line-height: 1.3;
            letter-spacing: -0.03em;
            color: var(--color-chalk);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
          ">Flow Agents</h1>

          <p class="animate-fade-up delay-100" style="
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--color-chalk-2);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
          ">the agent-facing vertical of Kontour Flow</p>

          <p class="animate-fade-up delay-200" style="
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            color: var(--color-chalk-2);
            line-height: 1.7;
            max-width: 520px;
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
          ">
            Agents are useful out of the box. They get fragile when work is
            long, parallel, risky, or knowledge-heavy — they skip verification,
            call partial work done, and lose the thread after compaction. Flow
            Agents installs one structured path into the runtime you already use,
            so a loose request becomes shaped work, plans, review, verification,
            and a release decision — with evidence the agent and the developer
            can both read back.
          </p>

          <div class="animate-fade-up delay-300" style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <a href="https://github.com/kontourai/flow-agents" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary" data-umami-event="flow-agents-hero-github">
              View on GitHub →
            </a>
            <a href="/flow" class="btn-ghost" data-umami-event="flow-agents-hero-flow">
              Built on Flow
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <Terminal class="animate-fade-in delay-300" title="install Flow Agents">
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">bash install.sh ~/dev/my-project</span></p>
          <br />
          <p class="muted">  installing Flow Agents bundle…</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ agents      Claude Code, Codex, Kiro, CI</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ skills      idea-to-backlog … learning-review</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ kits        Builder Kit</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ context     contracts, settings, hooks</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ evals       static · integration · behavioral</p>
          <br />
          <p class="muted">  workflow artifacts → .agents/flow-agents/</p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-3);">  ───────────────────────────────</p>
          <p class="info">  ready. ask your agent:</p>
          <p>  <span class="muted">"Use deliver for this issue."</span></p>
        </Terminal>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       The workflow
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section style="padding: 6rem var(--spacing-page);">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">One structured path</div>
      <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 1rem; max-width: 760px;">
        From a loose request to a release decision — gate by gate.
      </h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-3); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.65; max-width: 680px; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        Skills choose the right workflow, sidecars preserve state across
        compaction, gates catch stop-short behavior, and a finding or gap routes
        the work back instead of waving it through.
      </p>

      <div class="flow-steps" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(9, 1fr);
        gap: 0.5rem;
        align-items: stretch;
      ">
        {[
          'Idea', 'Backlog', 'Plan', 'Build', 'Review', 'Verify', 'Evidence', 'Release', 'Learn',
        ].map((step, i) => (
          <div key={step} style="
            position: relative;
            padding: 1.1rem 0.75rem;
            background: var(--color-ink-1);
            border: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
            border-radius: 6px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 0.4rem;
            text-align: center;
          ">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.58rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3);">0{i + 1}</span>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--color-chalk-2); letter-spacing: -0.01em;">{step}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p style="
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        color: var(--color-chalk-3);
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        margin-top: 1rem;
      ">
        review → finding routes back to build · verify → gap routes back to build · evidence → not-verified routes back to plan
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Three promises
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section style="
    padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    background: var(--color-ink-1);
  ">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="stack-mobile" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 1.5rem;
      ">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Stay on the path',
            color: 'var(--color-cobalt-2)',
            body: 'Loose requests turn into shaped work, plans, implementation waves, review, verification, and release decisions — without writing a perfect prompt every time.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Show the evidence',
            color: 'var(--color-green)',
            body: 'Acceptance criteria, test results, browser checks, governance reports, and gaps live in durable workflow artifacts the agent reads back — not in chat memory.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Use your runtime',
            color: 'var(--color-chalk-2)',
            body: 'Install one bundle across Claude Code, Codex, Kiro, and CI. The same workflow, without rewriting it for each tool.',
          },
        ].map(({ title, color, body }) => (
          <div key={title} class="card" style="padding: 2rem; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
            <div style={`
              position: absolute;
              top: 0;
              left: 0;
              right: 0;
              height: 2px;
              background: linear-gradient(90deg, ${color}, transparent);
            `}></div>
            <h3 style="
              font-family: var(--font-display);
              font-size: 1.35rem;
              font-weight: 400;
              color: var(--color-chalk);
              margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
              letter-spacing: -0.01em;
            ">{title}</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); line-height: 1.7;">{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Runtimes
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section style="padding: 6rem var(--spacing-page);">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Runs in the tools you already use</div>
      <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; max-width: 720px;">
        One bundle. Every runtime maps to its native shape.
      </h2>

      <div style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
      ">
        {[
          { rt: 'Claude Code', detail: 'Agents, skills, and hooks wired into the Claude Code harness.' },
          { rt: 'Codex', detail: 'The same workflow path mapped to Codex agent definitions.' },
          { rt: 'Kiro', detail: 'Runtime-specific hook wiring for Kiro sessions.' },
          { rt: 'GitHub Actions', detail: 'Carry the workflow and its evidence into CI agents.' },
        ].map(({ rt, detail }) => (
          <div key={rt} style="
            padding: 1.5rem;
            background: var(--color-ink-1);
            border: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
            border-radius: 6px;
          ">
            <div style="
              font-family: var(--font-display);
              font-size: 1.15rem;
              color: var(--color-chalk);
              margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
              letter-spacing: -0.01em;
            ">{rt}</div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">{detail}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p style="
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        color: var(--color-chalk-3);
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 720px;
      ">
        Runtime adapters translate one source configuration into each tool's
        native shape — so adding a runtime doesn't fork the workflow. Framework
        adapters for API-based agents (LangGraph, CrewAI, and peers) are on the
        roadmap.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Builder Kit
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section style="
    padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    background: var(--color-ink-1);
  ">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="stack-mobile" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 4rem;
        align-items: start;
      ">
        <div>
          <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-chalk-2);">Builder Kit</div>
          <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Opinionated building,<br />
            installed as a kit.
          </h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            The Builder Kit is the first Kontour-authored Flow Kit. It owns the
            Build path end to end — shaping, probing, planning, execution,
            verification, PR readiness, merge readiness, and learning — as
            workflows your agent invokes by name.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
            Flow Kits are runtime-neutral and authorable, so the Build path is a
            starting point — not the ceiling. Capture, Prepare, Understand, and
            Follow&nbsp;Up round out the work-mode model Flow Agents routes
            intent into.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.75rem;">
          {[
            { skill: 'idea-to-backlog', desc: 'Shape a raw idea into executable issues' },
            { skill: 'pull-work', desc: 'Select the next ready issue and hand it off' },
            { skill: 'plan-work', desc: 'Turn a goal into a structured execution plan' },
            { skill: 'execute-plan', desc: 'Run implementation in parallel waves' },
            { skill: 'review-work', desc: 'Critique before verification' },
            { skill: 'verify-work', desc: 'Prove the change actually works' },
            { skill: 'evidence-gate', desc: 'Decide if the work is trustworthy' },
            { skill: 'release-readiness', desc: 'Merge, release, or hold — with reasons' },
            { skill: 'deliver', desc: 'The full chain, end to end' },
            { skill: 'fix-bug', desc: 'Diagnose → fix → verify the regression' },
          ].map(({ skill, desc }) => (
            <div key={skill} style="
              display: flex;
              flex-direction: column;
              gap: 0.3rem;
              padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
              background: var(--color-ink-2);
              border: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
              border-radius: 4px;
            ">
              <code style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--color-chalk-2);">{skill}</code>
              <span style="font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); line-height: 1.4;">{desc}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       In practice
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section style="padding: 6rem var(--spacing-page); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="stack-mobile" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 4rem;
        align-items: center;
      ">
        <div>
          <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">In practice</div>
          <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            You ask for the outcome.<br />Flow Agents handles the scaffolding.
          </h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            No new CLI to memorize. You describe what you want in plain language;
            Flow Agents routes it to the right workflow and keeps the state,
            evidence, and next action durable — even across compaction, branch
            switches, and delegated subagents.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
            When evidence is missing, the workflow stops and says so, instead of
            summarizing unfinished work as done.
          </p>
        </div>

        <Terminal title="ask the agent">
          <p class="muted">  You</p>
          <p>  Use deliver for issue #214. Plan it, implement it,</p>
          <p>  verify it, and stop if evidence is missing.</p>
          <br />
          <p class="muted">  Flow Agents</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ plan-work     execution plan → 3 waves</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ execute-plan  implementation complete</p>
          <p class="pass">  ✓ review-work   1 finding → routed back → fixed</p>
          <p class="warn">  ✗ verify-work   browser check missing</p>
          <br />
          <p>  stopped at <span class="warn">evidence-gate</span></p>
          <p class="muted">  next: capture a browser check, then resume</p>
          <p class="muted">  state → .agents/flow-agents/runs/deliver-214/</p>
        </Terminal>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Evidence, governance, safety
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section style="
    padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    background: var(--color-ink-1);
  ">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">What keeps it honest</div>

      <div class="stack-mobile" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 1.5rem;
      ">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Durable artifacts',
            color: 'var(--color-green)',
            body: 'Workflow state, acceptance, evidence, critique, release, and learning records persist as inspectable sidecars under .agents/flow-agents/ — so a session can be resumed, audited, or handed off.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Optional governance',
            color: 'var(--color-cobalt-2)',
            body: 'Wire Veritas readiness reports in as a governance adapter to back merge decisions with repo-standard evidence. Optional, never mandatory — Flow Agents does not own the policy.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Deliberate execution',
            color: 'var(--color-gold)',
            body: 'Choose local, worktree, container, cloud, or privileged execution boundaries on purpose. Evals — static, integration, behavioral — keep the bundle honest as it changes.',
          },
        ].map(({ title, color, body }) => (
          <div key={title} class="card" style="padding: 1.75rem; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
            <div style={`
              position: absolute;
              top: 0;
              left: 0;
              right: 0;
              height: 2px;
              background: linear-gradient(90deg, ${color}, transparent);
            `}></div>
            <h3 style="
              font-family: var(--font-display);
              font-size: 1.25rem;
              font-weight: 400;
              color: var(--color-chalk);
              margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
              letter-spacing: -0.01em;
            ">{title}</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); line-height: 1.65;">{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Where it is today
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section style="padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="stack-mobile" style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 4rem;
        align-items: center;
      ">
        <div>
          <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-chalk-2);">Where it is today</div>
          <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Usable now.<br />Early by design.
          </h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            The core Build workflows run today. Flow Agents installs into a
            workspace from GitHub — it isn't on npm yet, and it's pre-1.0, with a
            phased rollout toward richer just-in-time guidance, more work modes,
            and deeper governance.
          </p>
          <a href="https://github.com/kontourai/flow-agents" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-umami-event="flow-agents-bottom-github" style="
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            color: var(--color-chalk-2);
            text-decoration: none;
          ">Read the docs on GitHub →</a>
        </div>

        <Terminal title="quickstart">
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">git clone github.com/kontourai/flow-agents</span></p>
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">cd flow-agents</span></p>
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">bash install.sh ~/dev/my-project</span></p>
          <br />
          <p class="muted">  then, in your agent:</p>
          <p>  <span class="muted">"Use idea-to-backlog for this feature</span></p>
          <p>  <span class="muted"> and create executable GitHub issues."</span></p>
          <br />
          <p>  <span class="muted">"Use fix-bug. Reproduce it, find root cause,</span></p>
          <p>  <span class="muted"> fix it, and verify the regression path."</span></p>
        </Terminal>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding: 3rem var(--spacing-page) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-3); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; font-style: italic; margin: 0;">
        Flow Agents is the agent-facing vertical of Kontour Flow. Flow owns the
        gates, transitions, and evidence; Flow Agents brings them — and optional
        Veritas governance — into the coding agents you already use.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer active="flow-agents" />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* The nine-step path steps down across breakpoints so the labels stay legible. */
  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .flow-steps { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr) !important; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .flow-steps { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr) !important; }
  }
</style>
